---
import ListItem from '../../components/text/ListItem.astro'
import PageTitle from '../../components/text/PageTitle.astro'
import Card from '../../components/ui/Card.astro'
import PageHeader from '../../components/ui/PageHeader.astro'
import ThemedSection from '../../components/ui/ThemedSection.astro'
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../../consts'
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout
  title={`Manual Lymphatic Drainage | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
  description="Learn about Manual Lymphatic Drainage (MLD), its indications, contraindications, and pricing at Lymphatic Specialists of Madison. Book your session today!"
>
  <PageHeader>
    <PageTitle class="mx-auto text-center text-primary">Manual Lymphatic Drainage</PageTitle>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-(--site-padding-base)">
      <div class="prose">
        <p class="h3 lsa lsa-slide-up no-repeat">
          <a href="/blog/manual-lymphatic-drainage-m-l-d" class="link link-accent"
            >Manual Lymphatic Drainage</a
          >, or MLD, is a gentle yet powerful form of bodywork that is intended to stimulate and
          encourage the natural movement of lymph fluid back into the heart and subsequently into
          the bloodstream.
        </p>
        <p class="lsa lsa-slide-up delay-100 no-repeat">
          It is a technique based on light rhythmic movements that mimic the rhythm of the body's
          lymphatic system. Lymphatic massage should always be done by a certified lymphatic
          specialist, as when done wrong could be ineffective or dangerous. The light pressure used
          for MLD is absolutely necessary in order not to occlude or compress the superficial
          location of the lymph vessels and nodes. MLD can be beneficial in reducing swelling,
          supporting immune function, and promoting relaxation.
        </p>
        <p class="lsa lsa-slide-up delay-200 no-repeat">
          If you are feeling a bit sluggish, experiencing mild to severe swelling, experiencing
          localized or systemic excess inflammation, recovering from an injury or surgery, or are
          interested in optimizing your immune system, MLD could be the therapeutic option for you.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="prose">
        <p class="lsa lsa-slide-up delay-300 no-repeat">
          Manual Lymphatic Drainage is also extremely effective in treating post-surgical swelling
          caused by DIEP flap reconstruction, mastectomy, liposuction, abdominoplasty, facelift,
          breast lift/reduction, and many, many other elective (and non-elective), reconstructive,
          and cosmetic surgeries. This treatment, in combination with scar tissue work, is also
          extremely effective in reducing the hardness or fibrosis that can be associated with
          liposuction.
        </p>
        <p class="lsa lsa-slide-up delay-400 no-repeat">
          Manual Lymphatic Drainage done at Lymphatic Specialists of Madison is performed by
          Courtney Rolnick, PT, DPT, CMLDT. Courtney was trained in the <a
            href="https://www.vodderschool.com/manual_lymph_drainage_overview2"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="link link-accent">Vodder Technique</a
          > through Klose Training with Nicola McGill. Courtney is highly trained with 9 years of experience
          in treating a variety of patients, including post-surgical patients, lipedema & lymphedema
          patients, and those with chronic health problems such as autoimmune disorders, Ehlers-Danlos
          syndrome, and Lyme.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="lsa lsa-slide-up delay-500 no-repeat">
      <a
        href="https://booksy.com/en-us/1554807_lymphatic-specialists-of-madison_massage_39663_madison#ba_s=sh_1"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="btn btn-primary"
      >
        Book Now
      </a>
    </div>
  </PageHeader>

  <main>
    <!-- Indications Section -->
    <section id="indications" class="pt-0">
      <div
        class="wrapper container lg:max-w-screen-xl flex flex-col gap-(--site-padding-md) mx-auto"
      >
        <h2 class="h1 text-primary text-center lsa lsa-slide-up no-repeat">Indications</h2>
        <p class="h4 text-center mx-auto lsa lsa-slide-up no-repeat">
